            "command": "git add src/filters.cc && git commit --author=\"John Wiegley <johnw@newartisans.com>\" -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nFix crash with --gain --subtotal on multi-commodity accounts\n\nWhen subtotal_posts accumulated postings for an account that held more\nthan one commodity, the raw post.amount values produced a BALANCE in the\nvalues map.  handle_value() then stored that BALANCE as compound_value\nwith POST_EXT_COMPOUND set.  Inside calc_posts, add_to_value() would\nbypass expression evaluation and add the BALANCE directly to the running\ntotal.  At that point the running total was already a 2-element sequence\nproduced by evaluating the --gain expression (amount, cost) for an\nearlier single-commodity posting; adding a BALANCE via push_back\nextended it to 3 elements.  A subsequent 2-element sequence from the\nnext posting then triggered \"Cannot add sequences of different lengths\".\n\nFix: evaluate amount_expr for each real posting before accumulating it\ninto the subtotalled values map.  This ensures the accumulated value is\nalways a 2-element sequence (holdings, total-cost) regardless of how\nmany commodities the account contains, so calc_posts always sees\nconsistently shaped values when building the running total.\n\nFixes issue #965.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"",
